        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In production-grade text-to-speech (TTS) systems, the challenges are clear: achieving sub-200ms latency, maintaining high audio fidelity, and enabling voice customization without prohibitive costs. Many TTS APIs compromise on one or more of these dimensions, forcing teams to choose between performance and flexibility. The Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice API, built on the Qwen3_TTS_12Hz_1_7B_CustomVoice model, is engineered to resolve these trade-offs with a 12Hz sampling rate optimized for real-time synthesis and a 1.7B-parameter architecture tailored for voice cloning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This post provides a concrete walkthrough for experienced API teams: from initial setup and request handling to performance tuning and cost management. You'll gain actionable insights into latency characteristics, error handling, and deployment patterns that ensure reliability at scale. By the end, you'll be equipped to integrate this API into your stack with confidence."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Capabilities of Qwen3 TTS CustomVoice"
